The hormonal treatment of dysfunctional uterine bleeding is most reasonable when the disorder is caused by a disturbed menstrual cycle. Thus, reproductive age is the domain of hormone therapy. Especially after menarche and in the premenopause, the hypothalamic-pituitary-gonadal axis shows unstable function causing several forms of bleeding disorders. Disturbances of cyclic function by endocrine or metabolic factors and organic genital lesions must be considered and should be included in the therapeutic concept.  
